HEADWORD: Squamozygomatic
<hw>Squa`mo*zyg`o*mat"ic</hw>
<pr>(skw⟦amac⟧`m⟦osl⟧*z⟦icr⟧g`⟦osl⟧*m⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to both the squamosal and
zygomatic bones; -- applied to a bone, or a center of ossification, in
some fetal skulls.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A squamozygomatic
bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
